post_text:
Pre-K Screening

The North Mac School District will hold developmental screenings for pre-school age children for the 2020-2021 school year on Monday, August 3rd (1:00 PM – 6:00 PM) and Tuesday, August 4th (9:00 AM-3:00 PM).

Screenings will be held at North Mac Elementary in Virden (755 W. Fortune St.). The screening will be open to any child who will be turning three (or older) this fall and is not age eligible for Kindergarten.

Please email Brooke Earley (BEarley@northmacschools.org) or call 965-5424 ext. 2602 to schedule an appointment. More details will be given when an appointment has been scheduled.

North Mac Graduation Live Stream (and On-Demand)
Graduation will be live streamed on the NFHS Network for FREE. All you have to do to view these events is go to www.nfhsnetwork.com and search for "North Mac" you will see both events listed. There is a 5pm ceremony and a 7pm ceremony. Students with Last Name beginning with letters A - J will be in the 5pm session. K - L will be in 7pm session.

If you cannot watch the live event, you can also watch the On-Demand recording at a later time.

post_text: Pre-K and Kindergarten classes at North Mac Elementary participated in "The Little Convincer" program. This was an interactive program taught by the Macoupin County Health Department. Students were taught why seat belts are worn, what can happen when they are not, and how a seat belt feels when properly secured. They met with each Pre-K class and weighed and measured each child to determine which car seat would be the best fit for them. Information was sent home with families to better inform them of the importance of proper car seat safety.

post_text:
Blue Ribbons and Blue Pinwheels throughout April show support for
Child Abuse Prevention Month!!

April is Child Abuse Prevention Month. Since 1983 communities across the country have used this month-long observance to increase awareness of child abuse and its prevention. It is a time when individuals, schools, businesses, hospitals, religious organizations, and social service agencies join together to raise awareness of child abuse and neglect.
Children are our future and their early years significantly impact their future success.
Contact Prevent Child Abuse Illinois at 217.522.1129 or www.preventchildabuseillinois.org for more information and ways you can make a difference.
In observance of this important cause, please wear blue ribbons and or display blue pinwheels throughout April to show your support!
You may order a pinwheel for $1.50 by contacting the elementary 965-5424 or intermediate schools 627-2419 by March 23. Proceeds will go to the Mini O’Beirne Nursery in Springfield.
Please wear Blue April 7 to show support of Child Abuse Prevention Month.

post_text:
The North Mac CUSD 34 Board of Education is conducting a search for a new superintendent. The selection of a new superintendent is probably the most important decision a board of education has to make; therefore, the Board has hired the Illinois Association of School Boards (IASB) to assist in this process.

The Board of Education is seeking staff, parent and community member input in the search process. The Board requests that everyone complete an online survey provided by the IASB. The results will be tallied and used by the Board and Screening Team to develop a brochure to advertise the position.

The link for the survey is: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/3W2W788
This survey will be available for completion until February 15, 2017 at 11:45 p.m.

Thank you for taking time to complete the survey.
